The National President of Association of Senior Civil Servants of Nigeria (ASCSN), Comrade Bobboi Bala Kaigama, has blamed state governments for deliberately refusing to pay the New National Minimum Wage, saying it is an acts of wickedness against workers under their payroll. He noted that the noncompliance to the directive of President Muhammadu Buhari on all state governments to start payment of the new minimum wage from January 1, 2020 as act of lack of political will. He said the move by Revenue Mobilization Allocation and Fiscal Commission (RMAFC) to trim the entitlements of political office holders was a welcomed development which can go a long way toward reduction of cost of governance. Speaking with LEADERSHIP, Kaigama charged Federal Government to take bold step to further reduce the cost governance through drastic trimming of the number of aides attached to political office holders. “We are calling on Federal Government to in addition to reduction of entitlements to political office holders, to trim the number of aides that are attached to political officeholders. The number of lawmakers, the Senate and House of Representatives should be reduced both at the federal and state levels. ‘’We don’t need so large number of lawmakers from states at the federal levels and even at state levels. Political class should sit down to deliberate on number that can come from each state and local government as representative in both the state and federal levels.’’ 